      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The temporary dips in labor participation during the stimulus periods were largely a function of massive, sudden economic shocks, not the safety net itself. These programs provided necessary lifelines during unprecedented crises, allowing people to weather the storm rather than being forced into immediate, precarious work. Attributing a broad participation dip solely to these temporary measures ignores the overwhelming external pressures of the pandemic economy.",
